Parliament, Tuesday 2 July 2019 – Today’s election of chairpersons of key oversight committees enables Parliament to exercise its law-making and oversight responsibilities, as required by the Constitution. Oversight committees are the engines that drives Parliament’s Constitutional functions of law-making, public involvement and oversight on behalf of the Houses of Parliament.
	
	After constituting themselves by, amongst others, electing their chairpersons, the committees will then determine their own programs, including which issues to prioritize.
	
	Committee chairpersons elected today are:
	
	Portfolio Committees National Assembly Standing Committees Today’s elections of chairpersons follow those last week of chairpersons of Select Committees of the National Council of Provinces.
	
	ISSUED BY THE PARLIAMENT OF THE REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA
